Eastern Cape Rural Development and Agrarian Reform MEC Nomakhosazana Meth has tested positive for the coronavirus. In a statement, the Office of the Premier says, MEC Meth is in self-isolation at her home. Spokesperson for the Premier, Mvusiwekhaya Sicwetsha, says Meth will continue with her duties. “She has decided to work from home during her 10 day period of isolation required for infection control and to prevent the spread of the virus. The Premier spoke to MEC Meth and on behalf of the Eastern Cape government and wished her a speedy recovery during this period. Because MEC Meth will be working from home Premier Mabuyane  will not be appointing an acting MEC in the department.” COVID-19 in Eastern Cape Eastern Cape is the third most affected province by the pandemic with 69 445 infections and 1393 deaths. Infographic: Latest COVID-19 statistics   Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape COVID-19 STATISTICS IN SOUTH AFRICA sabcnews.com |  SABC News channel | SABC Radio news SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 148854 53406 69445 13433 6068 15901 8987 2970 UNALLOCATED 50 AS AT 23 July 2020 1393 33 52 23 DEATHS 62 2780 1187 575 48 CONFIRMED CASES| 408 052 DEATHS|6093 TESTS CONDUCTED | 2 632 106 RECOVERIES | 236 260 CLOSED CASES | 242 353 88928 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); 